The input array `values` is not null.
The input array `edges` is not null.
The input integer `maxTime` is not negative.
The length of the input array `values` is equal to `n`.
The length of the input array `edges` is not greater than 2000.
The length of each subarray in the input array `edges` is equal to 3.
The values in the input array `edges` are valid node indices (between 0 and `n-1`).
The values in the input array `edges` are unique.
The values in the input array `values` are non-negative.
The values in the input array `values` are not greater than 10^8.
The values in the input array `edges` are valid edge weights (between 10 and 100).
The graph represented by the input array `edges` may not be connected.
